**Pattern 35: Agent-Based Modeling (ABM)**

Simulates complex systems through interacting agents. Reveals emergent behaviors and non-obvious system dynamics through multi-agent interaction.

**Key Components:**
- Multi-tier agent ecosystem
- Simple individual agent rules
- Trade/interaction networks
- Emergent system behaviors
- Disruption scenario injection
- Cascade effect measurement
- System-level analysis

**Business Value:**
- Identify critical single points of failure
- Test scenarios without real-world risk
- Optimize inventory and routing
- Prevent $200M+ losses
- Uncover non-intuitive optimizations
- Risk assessment at scale
